<title>DEAD TRENDS</title>

</head>

<body>

<h1 class="Barrio" style="background-color:ivory;">Dead Trends</h1>

<div class="ex1">Trends, like all good things, must come to an end. Although some trends like chunky sneakers can be given another life, most of them were so bad that we casted them to the back of our minds never to be seen again. Whether it's the low-rise jean fad of the 2000's we tried so hard to forget about or uggs with skirts, some trends deserve to die and stay dead. Here are some fashion DONTS to steer clear of in 2020.</div>

<h2 class="Barrio" style="background-color:ivory;">1. Crocs</h2>

<div class="ex1">These hideous shoes were originally made for boating yet somehow found their way on land in 2002. After making a comeback in 2019, we have come full circle with crocs back to sleeping with the fishes, where they belong.</div>

<img class="padding" src="img_Crocs.jpg" alt="Crocs" width="300" height="300">

<h2 class="Barrio" style="background-color:ivory;">2. Butterfly Clips</h2>

<div class="ex1">There are better ways to keep your hair out of your face then butterfly clips. This look is cheap and juvenile even on teens and should be left in the 90's with furbys. Do the right thing and use a regular clip or bobby pin like the rest of us.</div>

<img class="padding" src="img_ButterflyClips.jpg" alt="Butterfly Clips" width="250" height="300">

<h3 class="Barrio" style="background-color:ivory;">3. Dresses over jeans</h3>

<div class="ex1">Dresses over jeans has no place in the modern world. Why would you ruin your nice dress by wearing it with jeans? Why would you ruin your nice jeans by wearing them with a dress? This paring may of have been loved in the early 2000’s, but it’s 2020 now and we have standards.</div>

<img class="padding" src="img_DressesWithJeans.jpg" alt="Dresses With Jeans" width="160" height="300">

<h4 class="Barrio" style="background-color:ivory;">4. Denim Formalwear</h4>

<div class="ex1"> Just because Britney did it, doesnt mean you should do it. The only time where the recreation of this atrocity could be permitted is on halloween, because if there are any words to describe this look; scary would be one of them. </div>

<img class="padding" src="img_DenimDress.jpg" alt="Denim Formalwear" width="250" height="300">

